Now let's use formula $(1)$ and determine the lease payment that would be acceptable to the lessee as the value that makes the $\operatorname{NPV}$ and $\operatorname{NAL}$, zero:

$$
\begin{align*}
\operatorname{VPN}&= \$4,800,000 \hspace{2pt}–\hspace{2pt} \text{Annual cash flow}\times\frac{1-\dfrac{1}{1.0632^4}}{0.0632}\\[10pt] 
0 &= \$4,800,000 \hspace{2pt}–\hspace{2pt} \text{Annual cash flow}\times\frac{1-\dfrac{1}{1.0632^4}}{0.0632}
\end{align*}
$$
Then, 
$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Annual cash flow}&= \frac{\$4,800,000}{\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{1.0632^4}}{0.0632}}\\[30pt]
&=\frac{ \$4,800,000 }{3.4399}\\[10pt]
&=\$ 1,395,389.40
\end{align*}
$$

Now, for the lessor, we are assuming a $21$ percent tax rate too. So let's apply formula $(1)$ to the lessor's information:

$$
\begin{align*}
\operatorname{VPN}&= -\$4,800,000 \hspace{2pt}–\hspace{2pt} \text{Annual cash flow}\times\frac{1-\dfrac{1}{1.0632^4}}{0.0632}\\[10pt] 
0 &= -\$4,800,000 \hspace{2pt}–\hspace{2pt} \text{Annual cash flow}\times\frac{1-\dfrac{1}{1.0632^4}}{0.0632}
\end{align*}
$$
Then, 
$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Annual cash flow}&= -\frac{\$4,800,000}{\dfrac{1-\dfrac{1}{1.0632^4}}{0.0632}}\\[30pt]
&=-\frac{ \$4,800,000 }{3.4399}\\[10pt]
&=-\$ 1,395,389.40
\end{align*}
$$

Now,
$$
\begin{align*}
\text{Annual cash flow}&= \text{After tax lease payment} - \text{Depreciation tax shield}\\[10pt]
-\$1,395,389.40 &= \text{Lease value}\times(1-0.21) - \$252,000\\[10pt]
\text{Lease value}&= \frac{-\$1,395,389.40 + \$252,000}{(1-0.21)}\\[10pt]
&= -\frac{\$ 1,143,389.40}{ 0.79}\\[10pt]
&= \boxed{-\$ 1,447,328.35}
\end{align*}
$$
